review_blob: Aroma is smoked malts,almost like peat, raisins and coffee and toffee. Very dark brown to jet black with a medium brown head. Piney hope presence mixes with smoked malt character and bitter coffee on the finish that is not overpowering. Mouth feel is light like a regular IPA. Overall a very unique beer, as with most Mikkeller beers. Not sure I like the smokiness because it is reminiscent of a Rauchbier.

Fresh whole cone cascade hops from Sacramento area are well balanced with a sweetgrass malty backbone. Mild lemongrass aroma, light body and an easy drinking pale pale at 5.7% if your in the central valley and have a night to kill with some friends.

Reeks of vanilla, cream and whiskey barrels. Appearance is darker than a black steers tuckas on a moonless prairie night. taste ob vanilla chocolate and coffee with a boozy finish. Overall an amazing beer despite the crazy ass price.
